trans-unit.source: Represents an indexed collection of key/value pairs.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en indeksert samling av nøkkel/verdi-par.

trans-unit.source: IOrderedDictionary elements can be accessed either with the key or with the index.
trans-unit.target: IOrderedDictionary elementer kan åpnes med nøkkel eller med indeksen.

trans-unit.source: Each element is a key/value pair stored in a <xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry> structure.
trans-unit.target: Hvert element er en nøkkel/verdi-paret er lagret i en <xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>strukturen.</xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>

trans-unit.source: Each pair must have a unique key that is not `null`, but the value can be `null` and does not have to be unique.
trans-unit.target: Hvert par må ha en unik nøkkel som ikke er `null`, men verdien kan være `null` og har ikke være unik.

trans-unit.source: The IOrderedDictionary interface allows the contained keys and values to be enumerated, but it does not imply any particular sort order.
trans-unit.target: Grensesnittet IOrderedDictionary tillater inneholder nøkler og verdier som skal brukes, men det innebærer ikke en bestemt sorteringsrekkefølge.

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`For Each` in Visual Basic) returns an object of the type of the elements in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Den `foreach` -setningen for språket C# (`For Each` i Visual Basic) returnerer et objekt av typen for elementene i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Because each element of the <xref:System.Collections.IDictionary> is a key/value pair, the element type is not the type of the key or the type of the value.
trans-unit.target: Fordi hvert element i den <xref:System.Collections.IDictionary>er en nøkkel/verdi-paret elementtypen er ikke av nøkkelen eller type verdien.</xref:System.Collections.IDictionary>

trans-unit.source: Instead, the element type is <xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>, as the following example shows.
trans-unit.target: Elementtypen er i stedet <xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>, som eksemplet nedenfor viser.</xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>

trans-unit.source: [!code-cs[System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary_Implementation#03](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.collections.spe_7_1.cs)] [!code-cpp[System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary_Implementation#03](~/add/codesnippet/cpp/t-system.collections.spe_7_1.cpp)] [!code-vb[System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary_Implementation#03](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.collections.spe_7_1.vb)] The `foreach` statement is a wrapper around the enumerator, which allows only reading from, not writing to, the collection.
trans-unit.target: [!code-cs[System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary_Implementation#03](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.collections.spe_7_1.cs)][!code-cpp[System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary_Implementation#03](~/add/codesnippet/cpp/t-system.collections.spe_7_1.cpp)][!code-vb[System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary_Implementation#03](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.collections.spe_7_1.vb) ] den `foreach` setningen er en tekstbryting rundt enumeratoren, slik at bare lesing fra, ikke skriving til samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that iterates through the <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary"></xref> collection.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en opplisting som går gjennom den <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary"> </xref> samling.

trans-unit.source: [Visual Basic, C#] The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: [Visual Basic C#] Den `foreach` -setningen for språket C# (`for each` i Visual Basic) skjuler av hvor komplekse enumeratorene.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: Ved hjelp av derfor `foreach` anbefales i stedet for direkte manipulering enumeratoren.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratorene kan brukes til å lese data i samlingen, men de kan ikke brukes til å endre den underliggende samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: I utgangspunktet er enumeratoren plassert før det første elementet i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>henter også enumeratoren tilbake til denne plasseringen.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: At this position, the <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> property is undefined.
trans-unit.target: På denne plasseringen av <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>egenskapen er ikke definert.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Du må derfor kalle <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>å flytte enumeratoren til det første elementet i samlingen før leser <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>Returnerer det samme objektet før enten <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>eller <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>angir <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>til neste element.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>formidler slutten av samlingen enumeratoren er plassert etter det siste elementet i samlingen og <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerer `false`.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: Når enumeratoren er på denne plasseringen, etterfølgende kall til <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>også returnere `false`.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: Hvis siste kall til <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerte `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>er udefinert.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Angi <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>til det første elementet i samlingen på nytt, kan du kalle <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>etterfulgt av <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: En opplisting forblir gyldig så lenge samlingen forblir uendret.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du endrer til samlingen, for eksempel å legge til, endre eller slette elementer, enumeratoren ugyldiggjøres, og virkemåten er ikke definert.

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratoren har ikke eksklusiv tilgang til samlingen. lister opp i en samling er derfor gjelder ikke en sikker-prosedyre.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: For å garantere tråd sikkerhetsnivået under opplisting, kan du låse samlingen under hele opplistingen.

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: Du må implementere din egen synkronisering for å tillate samlingen for å få tilgang til flere tråder for lesing og skriving.

trans-unit.source: Inserts a key/value pair into the collection at the specified index.
trans-unit.target: Setter inn en nøkkel/verdi-paret i samlingen i den angitte indeksen.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary> accepts `null` as a valid value and allows duplicate elements.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary>godtar `null` som en gyldig verdi og tillater dupliserte elementer.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary>

trans-unit.source: If the `index` parameter is equal to <xref:System.Collections.ICollection.Count%2A>, the `value` parameter is added to the end of the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary> collection.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den `index` parameteren er lik <xref:System.Collections.ICollection.Count%2A>, `value` parameteren legges til slutten av den <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary>samlingen.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.IOrderedDictionary> </xref:System.Collections.ICollection.Count%2A>

trans-unit.source: In collections of contiguous elements, such as lists, the elements that follow the insertion point move down to accommodate the new element.
trans-unit.target: I samlinger sammenhengende elementer passer for eksempel lister, elementene som følger pekeren Flytt ned til det nye objektet.

trans-unit.source: If the collection is indexed, the indexes of the elements that are moved are also updated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis samlingen er indeksert, oppdateres også indeksene i elementer som er flyttet.

trans-unit.source: This behavior does not apply to collections where elements are conceptually grouped together, such as a hash table.
trans-unit.target: Dette gjelder ikke for samlinger der elementer begrepsmessig grupperes sammen, for eksempel en hash-tabell.

trans-unit.source: The zero-based index at which the key/value pair should be inserted.
